For this project, I use the the Toxic Release Inventory (TRI) dataset of the year 2018, which provides the information about toxic chemical releases and pollution prevention activities reported by industrial and federal facilities. Each observation is a facility with its latitude and longitude.

for index, tri in tri_table_top.iterrows():
    if tri["41. METAL"] == "YES":
        folium.Marker(location=[tri["12. LATITUDE"], tri["13. LONGITUDE"]],
                    icon=folium.Icon(color='red')).add_to(map)
        
    if tri["41. METAL"] == 'NO':
        folium.Marker(location=[tri["12. LATITUDE"], tri["13. LONGITUDE"]],
            icon=folium.Icon(color='blue')).add_to(map)
map

In this interactive map of TRI, I only present the facilities with the top 1% total quantity of chemical released as stack air emissions. Facilities are labeled with bule if the chemical released is a metal and with red if the chemical released is not a metal. From the map, we can tell that most of the facilities among the top polluters are releasing metal chemicals across US.
